article.headline: Georgia Southern 62, The Citadel 46
article.story: NORTH CHARLESTON, S.C. (AP) -- Louis Graham scored 15 points to help Georgia Southern to a 62-46 win over The Citadel on Wednesday night in the first round of the Southern Conference tournament. The sixth-seeded Eagles (15-15) will meet No. 3 seed College of Charleston in the quarterfinals Thursday. Georgia Southern raced out to a 25-9 lead with less than six minutes to go in the first half and led by 12 at the break. The Bulldogs cut the Eagles lead to 49-42 on Donny McClendon's 3-pointer with about seven minutes remaining, but could get no closer. Donte Gennie scored 14 points for Georgia Southern while Jimmy Tobias and Matt Fields each added 12. J'Mel Everhart led the Bulldogs with 13 points while McClendon added 10. The Citadel finished its season at 7-23 under first-year Coach Ed Conroy, the cousin of novelist Pat Conroy, who recalled his own days playing for the Bulldogs in his book "My Losing Season." Pat Conroy was on hand Wednesday, giving an interview to a local radio station.
